# Plan: Replace CI Script with GritQL Plugins

## Context

Testing revealed that Biome GritQL plugins DO work for file-scoped rules — the key is using `file($name, $body)` instead of bare `$filename`/`$program`. The `$name` variable contains the **full absolute path**, so regex needs `.*` anchors. Both filename- and content-based scoping work.

## What Already Exists (Previous Rounds)

- ✅ `biome.jsonc` override banning `chalk` in `src/commands/**/*.ts` via `noRestrictedImports`
- ✅ `src/commands/issue/view.ts` — `muted()` replaced with `isPlainOutput()` pattern
- ✅ `script/check-command-patterns.ts` + `check:commands` script + CI step (to be replaced)

## Plan: Replace `check-command-patterns.ts` with GritQL Plugins

The CI script approach works but GritQL plugins are better because they:
- Run as part of `bun run lint` (no separate CI step needed)
- Show inline diagnostics in the editor (IDE integration)
- Are suppressed per-line via `biome-ignore` (standard workflow)

### Files to Create

#### `lint-rules/no-stdout-write-in-commands.grit`

```grit
file($name, $body) where {
  $name <: r".*src/commands/.*",
  $body <: contains `stdout.write($args)` as $call,
  register_diagnostic(span=$call, message="Don't call stdout.write() in commands. Yield CommandOutput instead and let the buildCommand wrapper handle output rendering.")
}
```

#### `lint-rules/no-process-stdout-in-commands.grit`

```grit
file($name, $body) where {
  $name <: r".*src/commands/.*",
  $body <: contains `process.stdout` as $access,
  register_diagnostic(span=$access, message="Don't use process.stdout in commands. Yield CommandOutput and let the buildCommand wrapper handle output.")
}
```

### Files to Modify

#### `biome.jsonc`

Add `"plugins"` array at top level (after `"extends"`):

```jsonc
"plugins": [
  "./lint-rules/no-stdout-write-in-commands.grit",
  "./lint-rules/no-process-stdout-in-commands.grit"
],
```

### Files to Remove

- `script/check-command-patterns.ts` — replaced by GritQL plugins

#### `package.json`

Remove the `"check:commands"` script.

#### `.github/workflows/ci.yml`

Remove `- run: bun run check:commands` from the lint job (plugins run as part of `bun run lint`).

